                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3696: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="to"
                        >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Your 148, January 29, 5 p.m., last paragraph. The Department feels that, for
                    the present at least, authorities of the International Settlement and the
                    defense forces at Shanghai should confine their activities strictly to the
                    maintenance of peace and order in the Settlement and other areas in which they
                    have hitherto thus functioned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
